# 🚀 Ultimate VPN Setup & Kill Switch

Welcome to the quick and secure VPN setup guide! Follow these simple steps to get your secure tunnel up and running in minutes.

---

## 🛠️ Setup Steps

**1. Install Python**
> Ensure your system is ready by installing the core runtime environment from [python.org](https://www.python.org).

**2. Install Dependencies**
> Install the necessary libraries to handle network requests. Open your terminal and run:
```bash
pip install requests
```

**3. Install OpenVPN Client**
> Grab the official community client to establish the secure tunnel:
> 🔗 [openvpn.net/community-downloads](https://openvpn.net/community-downloads)

**4. Get a Configuration File (.ovpn)**
> Get a **FREE** Los Angeles `.ovpn` configuration file from trusted providers:
> - 🟢 **[VPNBook](https://www.vpnbook.com/)** (Free, pick a US server)
> - 🟣 **[ProtonVPN](https://protonvpn.com/)** (Free tier, pick US-LA)

**5. Local Setup**
> Place the downloaded `.ovpn` file exactly in **THIS** folder alongside your scripts.

**6. Ignition! 🪐**
> Launch the script to finalize setup.
> ⚠️ **Double-click `run.bat` AS ADMINISTRATOR**

---

## 🛡️ The Kill Switch

> [!WARNING]
> **Auto-Protection Active:** If the VPN drops, all internet is blocked automatically to prevent IP leaks! Click the disconnect button inside the app to restore normal internet.

### ⚡ Direct Override Commands

If you ever need to manually activate the kill switch via the terminal, open your Command Prompt as Administrator and run:

**1. Lock down the firewall:**
```cmd
netsh advfirewall set allprofiles firewallpolicy blockinbound,allowoutbound
```

**2. Terminate OpenVPN forcefully:**
```cmd
taskkill /F /IM openvpn.exe
```

---
*Stay secure! 🔒*

